  "name": {
    "short": "Tableau Server",
    "full": "Tableau Server"
  },
  "description": {
    "short": "Access Tableau's self-service analytics directly in Microsoft 365",
    "full": "The Tableau Server App for Microsoft 365 is an app designed for any business user. It is easier than ever to access, share, and collaborate on your Tableau dashboards within Microsoft Teams, PowerPoint (Preview), and Word (Preview). Access Tableau through the personal app, channels tabs, and during meetings, ensuring that your trusted data is always at your fingertips, empowering data-driven decision making. Please refer to our detailed [GitHub documentation](https://github.com/tableau/tableau-app-msft-teams) for installation guidance with Server environments. \n\nOnce installed, you can:\n - Integrate key Tableau visualization into your meetings in real-time\n - Share and pin your most relevant Tableau content in message and in channels\n - Embed Tableau visualizations into your PowerPoint presentations & Word documents\n\nNote: The Tableau Server app for Microsoft 365 requires a Tableau license to unlock its full potential. \nNote: Microsoft 365 Addins (PowerPoint, Word) are available in Public Preview.  To see if your Microsoft 365 app supports addins, refer to the [Microsoft documentation](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/office/dev/add-ins/develop/unified-manifest-overview#client-and-platform-support)\n\n[Installation Instructions](https://github.com/tableau/tableau-app-msft-teams)\n[Get Started](https://www.tableau.com/products/trial)\n[Contact Us](https://www.tableau.com/about/contact)"
  },
